list.name: Jon Seager
bio: Jon is VP Engineering, Enterprise Solutions at Canonical, leading the teams that deliver Juju and a suite of enterprise-ready operators for data platforms, machine learning operations, observability and more.

Following a degree in Computer Science, Jon's career started at the Royal Military Academy Sandhurst. He joined the Royal Corps of Signals where he played a key role in helping the UK define high-level doctrine for cyber operations and electronic warfare.

While working on next steps beyond the military, Jon spent 3 months participating in the Consensys Tachyon accelerator for early-stage blockchain startups. He subsequently worked for Thales UK, where he designed and built a public-cloud first development platform for UK government projects, bringing modern infrastructure-as-code and immutable infrastructure practices to a wider audience inside Thales.
Linux, open-source and tech interests aside, Jon is a husband and father with a keen interest in coffee, cars and bikes! You can find Jon on Twitter, LinkedIn and Github.

list.name: Jerzy Husakowski
bio: Jerzy is the Engineering Director responsible for MAAS, and together with his teams he builds the best bare-metal provisioning solution for private clouds small and large.

He received his MSc Eng degree in Computer Science from Gdańsk University of Technology, and spent two decades working on software in various industries. During his career, he built software for DVD recorders, light and sound experiences for hospital environments and hotels, medical software for proton beam treatment for cancer, video distribution for control rooms and exam rooms of x-ray systems, as well as software for statistical process control of high volume manufacturing of semiconductors. As a generalist with deep interest in software engineering, he enjoys building cool products and even cooler teams.
Jerzy lives in the Netherlands, loves reading and traveling with his partner. You can find him on LinkedIn and GitHub.

list.name: Reg Deraed
bio: Reg is Canonical's Field Sales Leader for Continental Europe. Graduated in Software Engineering from a French Grande Ecole, specialised in Telecommunications and Information Technology.
Reg has 22 years of experience in the IT sector, where he has had different various technical and commercial roles. He has been part of Canonical Ltd. for 6 years.
Reg lives in Buckinghamshire, England with his wife and three children.

list.name: Matthieu Clemenceau
bio: Matthieu is the Engineering Director responsible for the Ubuntu Foundations team. Matthieu and his team focus on supporting the core of the Ubuntu system, the base of the Ubuntu family of products and services.

Following a degree in Computer Science in France, Matthieu has spent his entire career working with Linux. Building embedded Linux distributions for ThinClients OEM in Europe within a startup in France then designing and developing a dedicated Linux distribution for Hewlett Packard ThinClients in the USA. As a software engineering leader, Matthieu enjoys building great teams and having fun creating cool software solutions.
Matthieu lives in the USA, in Houston Texas and loves playing guitar and fishing when he is not updating his home server with the latest Ubuntu. You can find him on LinkedIn and GitHub.

list.name: Ivo Jansky
bio: Ivo is the Director of Engineering, Commercial Systems at Canonical, leading teams that deliver backend services for Ubuntu Pro and Livepatch, administer Salesforce, automate business processes, operate a company-wide data lake, and develop a data science practice using open-source software.

While studying for a degree in Financial Markets, Ivo started working as a software engineer on software systems in the telco and banking sector, then moved to a management track leading backend development of a best-of-breed healthcare platform on the US market, and prior to joining Canonical led operations of software development centers in the Czech Republic and Spain.

As a hobby project, Ivo developed and operated a domain/mail/web-hosting service based on open-source software for about 10 years, which he values as a unique experience in delivering customer-focused and highly-available services in a highly competitive market.
Ivo is a father of two daughters and lives in Prague, Czech Republic. You can find Ivo on LinkedIn and GitHub.

list.name: Gabriel Aguiar Noury
bio: Gabriel is the Robotics and Mir Product Manager at Canonical, where he works to enable innovators and companies to deploy robotics and smart display solutions. Gabriel is a strong advocate for robotics startups, raising awareness of the barriers companies face from investors, policymakers and governmental authorities. He is also a promoter of security regulation in the robotics industry, helping robotics companies understand the need and the path toward secure deployments.

Gabriel is a mechatronic engineer, former entrepreneur and PhD in Robotic. Before joining Canonical, Gabriel worked in different ERDF initiatives supporting the development of innovation ecosystems for the robotic market through the creation of industry-wide platforms. This included running business incubator programmes and providing robotics SMEs with access to state-of-the-art technology, UX and UI evaluation services, and software security and deployment tooling.

list.name: Thibaut Rouffineau
bio: Thibaut is the VP of marketing at Canonical, leading a team of professionals who use technology to market/sell technology and value measurable impacts. Thibaut in numbers:

• Spent 100% of his career in tech, > 60% working for an operating system company / project and > 50% around open source
  • 100% accessible to everyone at Canonical
  • 100% dedicated to growing people in the marketing team
  • 70% marketer / 30% engineer
  • 10% of his wardrobe is Orange (mainly Ubuntu Orange)
  • 0% interested in fluffy marketing
When not at work, he spends his time competing in triathlons/endurance races, and recovers by reading a random assortment of books and measuring everything in his life.

list.name: Steve Barriault
bio: Steve Barriault is Vice-President Field Engineering IoT Worldwide at Canonical. He has 20 years of experience in field engineering, sales, technical marketing and business development in Devices and Embedded Software. He worked with clients from all over the world in a number of industries, such as Automotive, Avionics, Industrial Systems, Telecoms, Medical Devices and many more. He built and lef teams of engineers and salespeople in multiple countries. He speaks English, French and Chinese fluently plus Japanese, and holds multiple degrees in Business, Sciences, Computer Science and International Relations.

list.name: Hanna Neuborn
bio: As Global Head of Talent Science, Hanna is responsible for making sure that we are able to select industry leading talent here at Canonical. She leads a team of behavioural experts focussed on advising our Hiring Leads on best practice assessment methods.

Previously Hanna led hiring across the EMEA region at Dentsu International, a Global Marketing Technology organisation. Her key success in this role was launching  Talent Acquisition as a Centre of Excellence. Her earlier career was spent in the Financial Services industry.
Hanna is based in the UK. She holds a Bachelor's degree in Business and Product Management and a number of professional coaching and assessment qualifications.

list.name: Roshi Nouri
bio: Roshi is the EPMO Manager  for the EMEA and APAC region, managing a team of wonderful Project and Programme managers across many countries. She enjoys working with customers and always encourages her team to work smart. She joined Canonical as a project manager and managed some of the most interesting and complex projects before taking the management role.

Before joining Canonical six years ago Roshi spent most of her career at IBM. While at IBM she set up a number of Agile software factories for customers in the UK and led large Organisational Change and  IT Transformation programmes for customers in Banking, Retail, Government and Automotive.

Roshi holds a degree in Physics & Environmental Science and lives in London. She spends her free time reading historical novels, walking (Regent canal walk is her favorite route) and learning Italian without much success. She is also having a go at pottery.
Roshi is a proud mother of two boys and can be found on LinkedIn.

list.name: Regis Paquette
bio: Regis Paquette is Vice President Global Alliances, Channels, and Vertical Sales, at Canonical Group Ltd., the company behind Ubuntu, where he leads the company's global partner and channel business, reporting to the CEO. He joined Canonical in 2017 and drives the growth of the business with public clouds, OEMs, NEPs, VARs, Distributors, ISVs and Global System Integrators across the global portfolio.

Prior to joining Canonical, Regis spent 3 years in Nokia, where he created strategic alliances with all 3 major public cloud providers to facilitate hybrid cloud adoption by the telco industry, and was one of the founding members of the Telecom Infra Project with Facebook to bring innovation and opensource into telecom networks.

Regis has over 25 years experience in telecom, media and IT industry, with leadership roles in operations, product line management and strategic alliances, having managed global teams and lived in all 3 northern continents.

Regis holds an Engineering degree from CentraleSupelec, Post-Graduate Degree in Automatics and Signal Processing from Paris-Saclay, an MBA from Paris-Sorbonne, and is passionate about piloting, mountaineering and tinkering with the latest technologies.

list.name: Michael Cunningham
bio: Michael Cunningham is a Support Manager for the EMEA region in the Support Engineering team. As an engineer, Michael joined Canonical in 2013 and after a time implementing our products for customers, he moved to the Support team where he could help customers make the most of the products they were using.
Michael has been working in support, implementation and infrastructure operations for most of his career in industries such as transportation, telecommunications and managed services.
What does Michael enjoy the most about Canonical?

"I'd say the people and the products we make. I'm privileged to work with great people from all different backgrounds who have the vision to make the kinds of products that really make a difference. From Ubuntu Desktop to IoT to the datacentre, there are some great products that we can all contribute to."

list.name: John Meinel
bio: John is the Engineering Director for the Juju Team, helping to deliver not just the bits and bytes of software, but also logic around the operational characteristics of software (called Charms). Juju focuses on not just getting you software, but helping you to run and manage that software over its lifetime.

After completing a Master's Degree in Biomedical Engineering at the University of Iowa, he started working for a startup focused on Medical Imaging, but soon realized that his real passion was seeing the distribution of Open Source Software to as wide of an audience as possible. He joined Canonical in 2006, and has been in many different positions, always easing the path from an idea in a developers head to an end user that gets value from their effort.
John lives in Florida, USA, and is the proud father of one young man and one energetic puppy. You can find John on LinkedIn and Github.

list.name: Eric Chen
bio: Eric Chen is the team lead within the Managed-Service organization, responsible for the Bootstack DevOps Center. Bootstack DevOps Center is using Python to develop model-driven operations of managed service. They want to enable companies to run very efficient bare metal operations for high performance computing, private cloud, data lakes and analytics.

After completing a Computer Science and Engineering degree at National Taiwan University. Eric had served in various domains. Mobile software engineer in Mediatek. Data center researcher in Wiwynn. DevOps engineers in Trendmicro. In this decade, he focused on designing infrastructure of SaaS services on public and private clouds. He is an expert in the SRE (site reliability engineering) domain and keen to promote DevOps culture/practices. He joined Canonical at 2021.
Eric is based in Taiwan. In his spare time, he is interested in bridge games, hiking, biking and watching movies. You can find Eric on Linkedin.

list.name: Richard Zack
bio: Richard is the VP of Global Support Engineering at Canonical, leading the global teams that provide our 24/7 enterprise support service, software engineering, and professional services for mission-critical workloads.

Richard started his career with Linux at the age of 14, when he founded and built the first Internet Service Provider in Geauga County, Ohio. He later founded Pantek, an enterprise Linux and Open Source software services firm, one of the first providers of 24/7 enterprise support for Linux. Richard has experience across multiple sectors including media, defense, transportation, tech, and NGO's. He has been featured in many publications including ComputerWorld, USA Today, TechCrunch, and more.
Richard is also a father, husband, startup advisor, music lover and news junkie.

list.name: Brett Grandbois
bio: Brett Grandbois is an Engineering Director at Canonical leading the teams responsible for delivering the Linux kernel to a large number of internal and external consumers to the high standards for quality, performance and reliability that is expected by the Ubuntu community at large.

Following a degree in Mathematics from UCLA, Brett has spent the last 25 years working in and managing teams at various levels of the SW stack from bare metal HW controls, through OS internals on Linux, Windows, and various RTOS', through user space applications at the system and higher levels.  Brett also has experience in SW development on a variety of environments from embedded devices, to robotics, to standard desktop/server systems, to finally HPC storage systems.
Born and raised in Silicon Valley, but now based in Brisbane, Australia, Brett is an avid mountain biker and 4WD enthusiast and can be found on LinkedIn.

list.name: Varshi Gupta
bio: Varshi is the Engineering Director for IS DevOps teams at Canonical, with a mission of improving the experience of running complex business operations for ITOps and support teams. These teams are working on upgrading and building operators for easier installation, security upgrades, and day X maintenance of the applications managed by IT operations teams.

After graduation in Computer Science, Varshi developed enterprise software for multi-channel financial firms before moving to the United States for pursuing a Master's in Management and Information Systems. She has since then worked for healthcare, IT, and retail companies playing varied roles in software development, architecture, and product management. Beyond her usual job duties, she serves as an advisor for technical startups helping them think through their product journeys.
Varshi is currently living in Canada and enjoys reading, hiking, traveling, meeting new people, and listening to podcasts.

list.name: Neil French
bio: Neil is the Chief Operating Officer at Canonical, leading the teams that own the internal machinery of the business to serve our staff and customers better.  His team drives policies, processes and systems across Finance, Legal, Sales Operations, People, Program Management, Workspaces, Travel and Administration.

Prior to joining Canonical over ten years ago, he worked across hardware, software, networking and SaaS businesses, in roles spanning strategy consulting, product management, product marketing and sales operations.  He holds degrees in Engineering Science from Oxford University and Management from Massachusetts Institute of Technology.

He lives in London, England and when not working you'll find him walking the dog, working his vegetable garden, mending things the family breaks, and suffering the highs and lows of being a season ticket holder at Tottenham Hotspur Football Club. He also hangs out on LinkedIn and Twitter.

list.name: Ante Karamatić
bio: Ante Karamatić is the Engineering Director within the Support Engineering organization, responsible for the Sustaining Engineering Group. Sustaining Engineering Group is responsible for providing software engineering support to our customers. We are typically the last line of support, providing subject matter expertise in various areas and patches for software defects.

Ante joined Canonical in 2011. as a software engineer. Within his tenure at Canonical, he served in various roles, but all have been engineering and customer facing. Before joining Canonical, Ante was an active member of the Ubuntu, mostyl server, community since 2005. Education wise, he holds a Masters degree in civil engineering from University of Zagreb, as well as an Executive MBA degree.
Based in Croatia, in his spare time, he likes to spend time with his family and catch some slopes with some of his snowboarding buddies. And of course, geek out on solar panels and EVs.

list.name: Rex Tsai
bio: Rex Tsai is the Director of Device Enablement Team, responsible for integrating optimized and customized Ubuntu OEM solutions for devices, including Personal Computer, Internet of Things (IoT), Industrial Automation, Robotics, Automotive, SmartNIC and many other use cases on the edge computing.
Rex joined Canonical in Jun 2011 as software engineer, has served in various roles, from engineering and customer facing

Based in Taipei, Taiwan. In his spare time, he likes to spend time doing outdoor activities, including hiking, backpacking, and scuba diving. He is also involved in non-profit organization activities, by organizing open source software events or contributing open source software to civic technology.

list.name: Matias Piipari
bio: Matias is the Engineering Director responsible for Hardware Certification and Solutions QA teams.

Together with his teams he maintains the Ubuntu Hardware Certification test suite, as well as tools and services that support Canonical's unparalleled hardware compatibility story for popular hardware from major OEMs, ODMs and IHVs. With the Solutions QA team, Matias' focus is on the other hand on Canonical's cloud solutions, building tools, procedures and test pipelines that support the successful delivery of distributed systems that make up Canonical's cloud operations from metal to container.

Matias graduated in 2010 with a PhD in computational biology from University of Cambridge, having focused on developing and applying Machine Learning methods to genomics data. He took part as CTO in building multiple design award winning software for scientists and co-founded a company to build an open source, collaborative scientific writing tool, holding both senior product and engineering leadership roles before joining Canonical.
Matias is based in Finland. He is a modular synthesizer, photography and running nerd, and you can find him on LinkedIn, GitHub, GitLab (and Spotify).

list.name: Eric Gelinas
bio: Eric is the Engineering Director responsible for LXD, Anbox and Multipass. His focus is on building software development teams that are crafting components of modern cloud stacks.

Following degrees in Computer Engineering and Operations Research, Eric has devoted his entire career to building software and software teams. With deep expertise in scheduling and infrastructure, he enjoys working with highly specialised resources and challenging projects.
Based in Montréal Canada, Eric lives at the heart of the city, runs a tiny private cloud at home for fun and raises bees on the roof of his town house with his life partner.

list.name: Janaina Ruas
bio: Janaina is Director of Engineering, for Partner Engineering at Canonical, leading the teams that partner with major Silicon companies to optimize Ubuntu for their latest platforms, for iot devices, desktop and server solutions.

Janaina's career started at Itautec, working on banking automation systems, followed by IBM where she worked on distributed systems for the telecom industry. After IBM she worked for BankBoston, developing enterprise banking systems on Unix, but quickly moved to Eldorado Research Institute, which she helped grow from a small institute of 50 people to one of the main R&D institutes in the country with more than 1000 people. At Eldorado she led software R&D projects in partnership with worldwide desktop, server and mobile phone manufactures as well as later supporting the digital transformation projects for many other industries, such as oil & gas, health and agritech.

Following a degree in Computer Engineering, and an MBA in Business Management, she has worked in many roles including Software Developer, Engineering Manager, Chief Innovation Office, Senior Manager, Engineering Director and Software R&D Executive.
Janaina is a wife and mother of two sons and lives in Brazil, and aside from tech interests, Jana is also interested in yoga, mediation and travel! You can find Janaina on LinkedIn.

list.name: Tej Makani
bio: Hi there,

Thank you for expressing an interest in working at Canonical. We really appreciate the time and effort invested in this process and I wanted to take a few moments to give you a brief overview of my role, the EA team and what we're looking for in our new colleague.
I joined Canonical in November 2021, I live in the UK and am the proud parent of a grumpy cat and mischievous puppy.

In addition to being an EA at Canonical, I'm also one of many Hiring Leads here. Hiring Leads are a group of individuals, from different levels of the company, whose mission is to help bring in the best talent. We do this by carefully reviewing applications, assessments, interviewer feedback and determining which candidates we will progress to the next stage.

Alongside this, I work with a fantastic team of EAs. Our team is key in unifying our company mission and vision through the coordination of global events, travel and expense management and the  implementation of policies and procedures. We also work closely with senior colleagues and their teams, helping drive success through administrative support. As a remote-first business, we want every colleague, no matter how remote a region they're in, to feel 'plugged in' and part of Canonical's journey.

The EA team is wonderfully diverse and we enjoy working, supporting and laughing alongside one another. We're looking for someone who will compliment our team and energy. We're not expecting candidates to already have administrative experience, but a strong academic background is important. So, if you're a bright, eager to learn, tech savvy team player, then this role is perfect for you!

I hope this brief insight into Canonical and the EA team has inspired you to complete the upcoming assessments. The assessments allow us to gain a much deeper understanding of your skills, experience and personality, so please do take the time to complete them. I remember doing my written assessment and sincerely enjoyed the chance to reflect on my career - past, present and future. I hope you find the process just as insightful.
If you have any questions or simply want to learn more about my crazy pets, please send me an email.
Good luck!
Tej

list.name: Jonathan Simkins
bio: Jonathan Simkins is the chief financial officer at Canonical and is responsible for leading the company's worldwide finance and security organizations.  Jonathan joined Canonical in 2021, and is deeply involved in the company's strategy development, operations and overall execution of the company's path to the public equity markets.

Prior to Canonical, Jonathan served as the CFO for Tappit, Appgate and CyberGRX, and was the founder and CEO of Visum Cyber, which was successfully exited via M&A.  Jonathan also spent 5 years at HSBC in strategy, corporate development and operations roles, and prior to that he was an investment banker focused on technology M&A and private placements.
Jonathan earned a master's degree in business administration from the University of Oxford and a bachelor's degree in business administration and finance from the University of Washington.

list.name: Eric St-Jean
bio: Éric is the Engineering Director overseeing the engineering work for our public cloud partners, and responsible for the engineering relationship with those partners. His teams are responsible for everything Ubuntu on public clouds, which represents tens of billions of instance hours of usage a year.

Éric is an aerospace engineer by training, and dabbled in very low level electronics and systems engineering for the space sector before gradually moving up the stack through aviation, SAAS and cloud-based SAAS  businesses over the years before joining Canonical in 2020. He loves working on multiple strategic projects involving complex systems and many internal and external teams.
He is based outside Montréal, Canada, on a dirt road and enjoys nature and the great outdoors.

list.name: Eric Driffort
bio: Eric Driffort is Vice President of Global Sales at Canonical Group Ltd, the company behind Ubuntu. He leads the direct datacenter sales org, reporting directly to the CEO. He joined Canonical in 2016 and has consistently driven the growth of the enterprise business.

Prior to joining Canonical, Eric spent 18 years at Serena Software as the EMEA General Manager,  partnering with the World's most recognisable brands. He is a results-oriented enterprise software business leader with experience working in Cloud, Digital Transformation and Business Intelligence.
Eric has over 25 years of experience in Software and lives between London and Paris.
Eric holds a Master of Computer Applications and a PhD in International Marketing from Paris DAuphine. When not working, he plays tennis and is a drummer in a rock band.

list.name: Anthony Dillon
bio: Anthony is a Director of Engineering at Canonical. Leading the Web Engineering teams, delivering a range of UI projects including web applications, websites, the Canonical design system (Vanilla), and more.

Following a degree in Computer Science at the University of Essex, Ant's jumped straight into his career with the Gorillaz. Where he developed their online presents and marketing. Including many immersive online games for which he has been rewarded a Webby.

Since joining Canonical many years ago, Ant has helped to rapidly grow the organisation's design scale, architecture and engineering practices. Passionate about open source and excels in developing solid design systems to enable rapid, sustainable delivery through decentralised decision-making with a focus on results.
When not working, Anthony enjoys running, playing football and spending time with his family. You can find Ant on LinkedIn and GitHub.

list.name: Massimiliano Gori
bio: Massi is a Security Product Manager focusing on the area of Identity and Access Management across both the Ubuntu operating system and Canonical infrastructure offerings. Massi is involved in widening Ubuntu authentication options, improving the way the system is represented in mobile device management tools and delivering a new identity and access management platform to be adopted by all Canonical products. Massi is also involved in improving Canonical corporate security and build integrity story.

Massi started his career as an identity and access management developer, but soon transitioned to cybersecurity focused roles, working with government organisations to improve the cyber resilience of critical national infrastructure firms across the Uk and Italy. Massi holds an MBA from the Stanford Graduate School of Business and a degree from Imperial College London.
Outside of work Massi enjoys swimming, cooking and going to the local go kart track to ride his motard motorcycle.

list.name: Malachy Casey
bio: Malachy Casey is Leader of our Global Accounts Group at Canonical Group Ltd., the company behind Ubuntu. He joined Canonical in January 2022 and has a strong track record of building and scaling large scale global customer field sales teams.

Prior to joining Canonical, Malachy has had senior leadership roles, building out AWS' Global Accounts organization, managing Globals at VMware and various leadership positions at RedHat and Cisco. He has over 25 years experience in Infrastructure, Software and Cloud successfully providing multiple leading partnerships with the world's leading companies.
In his spare time, he focuses on his outdoor sports interests, hobbies and time with his family.

list.name: Marco Ciatti
bio: Marco is the Global Sales Development Manager at Canonical and is responsible for generating over 95% of the net new sales pipeline. His team is considered the “Sales Academy” of Canonical, and it's focused on developing and nurturing marketing and sales skills in the new generation of tech sellers.

Prior to working at Canonical, Marco led the creation of a new robotic division in an asset management company, making it the first worldwide company to rent long-term industrial robots to the largest manufacturing companies in Europe. Finally, he contributed to creating a pipeline of $10M in less than nine months.

Marco is based in London, UK and holds a Bachelor's degree in Mechanical Engineering from the University of Leicester. When not working, you'll find him playing all kinds of sports (football, skiing, ping-pong, pool, and many more) and learning new recipes to cook for his friends and family.

list.name: Andrew Cloke
bio: Andrew is a manager in the Public Cloud team, responsible for delivering fresh Ubuntu cloud images that meet the needs of many teams in the Google Cloud Platform.

With 25 years experience leading, managing and building server and embedded software teams, Andrew has a proven track record executing projects, working closely with customers and collaborating with diverse internal and external stakeholders.

His career started in Philips Research labs and quickly progressed into large scale software development - first with Psion, Symbian and Nokia developing mobile phone OS software, then SaaS solutions with Bloomberg, and now server-focused development with Canonical. He has worked in many roles including Software Developer, Engineering Manager, Chief Technology Architect, Strategy Director and Engineering Director. With every role he has had a keen focus on business, people and technology.
Andrew is based in the leafy London suburbs, and is a keen, but very amateur runner who enjoys escaping to the countryside whenever possible.

list.name: Camille Rodriguez
bio: Camille works as a Field Engineering Manager at Canonical, where she designs and deploys private clouds, with technologies such as Kubernetes and Openstack, Juju Charms, MAAS, and other open-source projects. She has been part of the Data Center Field Engineering department for over 3 years and worked 2 years before that in Openstack Operations for a major Telco in Canada. She also leads the Women's Resource Group at Canonical and is a hiring lead for the Field Engineering Department.

Originally from Montréal, Canada, Camille studied Physics Engineering at Polytechnique Montréal, before shifting her career towards Cloud Computing. She enjoys coding, networking with people, volleyball, hiking and outdoors.

list.name: Nobuto Murata
bio: Nobuto is based in Tokyo, Japan, currently leading the APAC Data Center Field Engineering team at Canonical and interacting with customers using OpenStack, Kubernetes and more technologies. Our team is responsible for a wider range of customer-facing activities including presales, delivery, consulting and engineering.

I was an Ubuntu enthusiast and that's how I started my career. I've been working for Canonical for 9 years now and experienced multiple roles in the company such as on-site support engineer to a large-scale customer, architecting clouds and tackling real-world issues at customer sites, and leading a team.

list.name: Calvin Hartwell
bio: Calvin has been at Canonical since 2017 and currently works as a Director in the Data Center (DC) Field Engineering team. Field Engineering is responsible for delivering and architecting solutions for customers using Canonical's Data Center products such as Kubernetes, Openstack and Ubuntu Server. The department is made up of multiple teams and delivers solutions in EMEA, APAC and the US for a wide range of different verticals.

Based in Chelmsford, the birthplace of radio, Calvin studied Computer Science at Loughborough University and has previously worked at Intel, British Telecom (BT) and Red Hat. Calvin enjoys datacenter infrastructure, programming, photography, horology and competitive shooting.

list.name: Shaun Murphy
bio: Shaun Murphy is the director and head of security engineering at Canonical and manages the security certification and technology groups. The security certification group empowers users to run regulated and high security workloads on Ubuntu and the technology group provides the  domain expertise in confidential computing, secure boot, apparmor and many more security technologies used across Canonical's portfolio of products.

Shaun Murphy got his start in security engineering back in the late 1990s by securing intelligent payphones and implementing cryptographic authentication and privacy in telecommunications. Shaun's career continued as a subject matter expert in cybersecurity and cryptography for various US Department of Defense projects and he started a company that focused on securing cloud based storage and communication prior to joining Canonical. Shaun holds a Bachelor's and Master's of Computer Engineering and recently completed his executive leadership program at MIT Sloan.
Shaun is a proud father of three children and enjoys volunteering his time and resources to teach children technology, security and privacy.

list.name: Kent Lin
bio: Kent Lin is the Engineering Manager responsible for the OEM QA team. His team works with all the engineering teams in Canonical, OEM, and ODM customers, to bring Ubuntu directly to millions of users by delivering certified Ubuntu laptops, desktops, IoT, and other computing devices.

Following dual master degrees in Electrical Engineering and Construction Management from the University of Southern California, he has worked in many roles including Software Developer in the digital electronics manufacturer, Field Engineer in the IC design house, Project Manager in the systems software provider, and Chief Product Officer in the AI startup.
Kent is based in Taipei, Taiwan, and aside from work, Kent is also interested in jogging, biking, skiing, and travel! You can find Kent on LinkedIn.

list.name: Daniele Procida
bio: Daniele Procida is a Director of Engineering at Canonical. He leads Documentation Practice throughout the organisation.

Canonical's ambition is to set standards of excellence in software product documentation for the entire industry. Daniele defines Canonical's long-term strategy towards this ambition, and guides the company's activities, processes and objectives along the way.

Daniele is the creator of the widely-adopted Diátaxis documentation approach. He previously worked at Divio, and has been a long-term participant in open-source software projects and communities, notably Python and Django.

Since 2015 he has been engaged in the pan-African Python movement, helping to organise African PyCons - including the first-ever PyCon Africa in 2019 - and build open-source software communities in Namibia, Ghana and other nations.
Daniele enjoys machines of all kinds, especially cameras, bicycles and low-cost robotics projects.
GitHub and the very occasional Twitter

list.name: Mike McGuire
bio: Mike is the Devices Project Management Director at Canonical, leading the teams that own the delivery of IoT, Silicon, and PC projects and programs to Canonicals customers and partners. His team drives processes and delivery across the engineering teams responsible for devices and partnership deliveries.

Prior to joining Canonical over thirteen years ago, Mike worked across Industrial automation, software, telecom, and networking businesses, in roles spanning project/program management, engineering, and quality. He holds bachelor's and masters degrees in Electrical Engineering from the University of British Columbia and Simon Fraser University, respectively. Mike is also a P.Eng and is PMI PMP certified.

Mike is a father of two children and lives in Kelowna, Canada. When not working youll find him walking the dog, riding off-road motorcycles with his wife, and training for the next half-marathon. You can find Mike on LinkedIn.

list.name: Guillaume Belanger
bio: Guillaume is an engineering manager at Canonical where his team's mission is to provide automated, secure, and affordable mobile networks to the world. They take popular telecommunications projects like Magma and make them easy to install and operate.

Before joining Canonical, he worked at one of Canada's largest telecommunications companies as a senior enterprise architect where he led teams to automate operations of large scale networks. He completed his studies at Polytechnique Montreal where he graduated in Engineering Physics.
Outside of work, you may spot Guillaume on his bike or in a record store around Montreal. You can also find him on LinkedIn and Github.

list.name: Billy Olsen
bio: Billy is the Engineering Director for the OpenStack organisation, with a mission to deliver fully automated virtual infrastructure solutions for public and private clouds on Ubuntu utilising pure Open Source Software including OpenStack, Ceph, OVN and others. His organisation focuses both  on making these software components easily consumable by institutions everywhere and bringing ease of use by providing automated deployment solutions leveraging Juju and MAAS.

After completing a Computer Science and Engineering degree at Northern Arizona University, he joined IBM to work on enterprise-grade storage systems and storage management software. He left IBM to seek an opportunity where he could explore his love of and contribute directly to open source, joining Canonical in 2014 to focus on OpenStack.

Work interests aside, Billy is a husband and father with a passion for amateur rocketry. He particularly enjoys building scale models of actual flight vehicles that are suitable for flight in low, medium and high power rocketry. You can find Billy on LinkedIn and Github.

list.name: Alex Burrage
bio: Alex is the Director of Security Maintenance at Canonical, responsible for understanding and managing the security risk of all Canonical users. This means monitoring and responding to security vulnerabilities that affect Ubuntu and our other maintained software, and his team is responsible for the security of thousands of items of open source software.

His journey began with a PhD in Cryptography, and has been focused on Security ever since. He has worked in various technical engineering roles prior to Canonical, spanning large scale devices that ship to millions of users, to highly bespoke deployments for very high grade security customers. It has covered mobile devices, desktop applications, server deployments and embedded firmware, but always with the goal of providing the best security service possible.
Alex is based in the UK near Edinburgh, and is a proud dad of two small children and two large cats.

list.name: Jean-Baptiste Lallement
bio: Jean-Baptiste is the Engineering Manager responsible for the Enterprise Desktop. The mission of his team is to deliver high-quality, enterprise-grade features among which integration with corporate directories (Active Directory, Azure), Disk encryption or VDI solutions. His team also provides support to field engineering and sales teams.

Jean-Baptiste joined Canonical in 2010 as a QA Engineer, then as QA Manager on the Ubuntu Phone project, and finally moved to Desktop projects. Before joining Canonical, Jean-Baptiste worked as CTO for a major French telco. Engineer at heart with 25 years of experience, Jean-Baptiste has always been a contributor and advocate of Linux, Ubuntu and Open Source in general, ever since he graduated from the University of Reims in Computer Science.
Jean-Baptiste lives in Britany, France, where he enjoys hiking, sea activities and reading. You can also find him on GitHub and LinkedIn.

list.name: Christopher Newcomer
bio: Christopher Newcomer is a Support Manager for the AMER region in the Support Engineering team. As an engineer, Christopher joined Canonical in 2017 and worked directly with customers to help them to fully utilize all of Canonical's products.

Christopher has been working in technical support for most of his career while working for hardware and software vendors, such as Sun Microsystems, Oracle, and Nexenta. He is passionate about support and providing an excellent customer experience.
Christopher lives in the USA in a suburb of Madison, Wisconsin. He enjoys downhill skiing, going to the gym, and home remodeling.

list.name: Michael Croft-White
bio: Michael is an Engineering Director in Canonical's Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) division. He focuses on the Internet of Things (IoT) and telemetry systems.

Michael has an undergraduate degree in Computer Science and PhD in Engineering. His early career was focused on motorsport working for various top flight teams in F1, WRC, FormulaE and Le Mans. He enjoys technical challenges and finding the extremes of performance in all technical fields.
Michael lives on the South Coast of the UK and enjoys being active in the great outdoors and building his own house when not sat in front of his computers.

list.name: Bryan Everly
bio: Bryan is the Vice President of Engineering for Canonical's Software as a Service (SaaS) applications.  These applications include the Snap and Charm Stores, Launchpad, Landscape and Canonical's Internet of Things (IoT) device management and telemetry software.

Bryan's undergraduate degree is in Computer Science and he holds a Masters Degree in Cybersecurity from the University of California Berkeley.  Over his career, Bryan has worked in a number of software companies such as Software Artistry, Tivoli Systems, IBM, PeopleStrategy, ExactTarget and Teradata.  He enjoys building software that solves real world problems and has specialized in SaaS applications since 2001.

Bryan lives in the USA in Indianapolis Indiana and loves playing bass guitar and working on cars when he isn't working on open source projects or maintaining his home lab.  You can find him on [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/bryaneverly), [GitHub](https://github.com/bceverly) and at his own blog - [FunctionallyParanoid](https://functionallyparanoid.com).

list.name: Mark Shuttleworth
bio: Mark is the founder and CEO of Canonical. He has built a number of business and philanthropic initiatives over the years, starting with Thawte in 1996. He plays an active role in Canonical product and engineering leadership, believing that the company serves customers and community best when we capture the essence of open source in the easiest-to-use and most reliable-to-deploy form.

list.name: Katherine Ollerhead
bio: Katherine Ollerhead is the Director of Legal and Company Secretary for Canonical. Katherine is responsible for managing all legal matters for the Canonical group of companies, including transaction support, intellectual property, property matters, employment, governance and company secretarial.
Katherine has worked in law for over 20 years and has been with Canonical for over 10 years. Prior to Canonical Katherine was an IT and outsourcing lawyer at a leading London law firm.
Katherine started life in London where she continues to live with her own family. She describes practicing law as her vocation.

list.name: Kristofer Tingdahl
bio: I have been Engineering director - Information Services at Canonical since February 2022.

Information Services is driven by the vision to deliver highly competitive and secure compute services to Canonical's teams and clients as well as the Ubuntu community, by showcasing and refining Canonical's technologies and excellency on a full stack basis.

Status quo is not an option here : we are constantly challenging ourselves  to break new grounds, and improve the high level of self service and self driving systems of our Open Source based operation.

My career path has not been straight: I am a trained geologist, turned AI scientist, C++ software developer, designer, only to discover that I thrive at mentoring & coaching, finance, accounting and all aspects of running a business in the technology sector.
I am looking for new team members that share my passion to find solutions to complex problems, who can keep practical while keeping in mind the big picture and long term objectives.
How do we get there? Let's start by letting every decision we do be oriented towards the overarching goal.
Do you want to join me on this quest?

list.name: Luca de Pasqua
bio: Luca is the Director of Desktop Support at Canonical, based in Italy. The Desktop Support Group he oversees  is a global team of Linux and open source engineers supporting Ubuntu desktop solutions and open source applications for Canonical Customers.

Luca joined Canonical in 2022, and holds a Software Engineering degree. He worked 10 years at Amazon in various roles, but all in support engineering and always customer facing. He worked at the launch of Amazon.it and .es, and Amazon Business in the US, and built support teams and businesses both in EMEA and Americas. Before joining Canonical, he worked as Global Director of Support for Wolters Kluwer.
In his spare time he loves to cook, try out new food, travel and spend time with his family. Unless he is tinkering with his latest tech/geek toy.

list.name: Simon Aronsson
bio: Simon is the Engineering Manager for the Observability team at Canonical, where he works at making sure all of Canonical’s products and projects come with excellent observability support out of the box. As Simon has been doing quite a lot of public speaking at different conferences, there is a fair chance that you might have either met him, or heard him speak about observability, devops, reliability or go prior to this.

Prior to joining Canonical, Simon worked at k6, a reliability testing company that later went on to become part of Grafana Labs. Throughout his career, he’s been appointed a Docker Captain, as well as a Google Developer Expert in the Cloud / Modern Architecture category. He is also a frequent contributor to external open source projects, mainly through containrrr/watchtower and containrrr/shoutrrr.
Aside from tech, Simon is very interested in outdoorsy activities like skiing, foraging, hiking. He is a dog dad of two, one being an italian greyhound and the other one being a pudelpointer.
You can find Simon in various places like dev.to, Twitter and LinkedIn.

list.name: Jey Jeganathan
bio: Jey is the Global Head of Workplace Engineering at Canonical. As Canonical grows rapidly, now more than ever, it's important to explore what contributes to happiness and productivity at work. Made up of web engineers, user experience designers, data scientists, and psychologists, the Workplace Engineering team leverages internal feedback, latest research, organisational data, and advanced analytics to improve the employment experience at Canonical, and help foster a highly engaged workforce to lead us in enterprise open source.

Prior to joining Canonical, Jey worked in Telecom, Software, Data Science, and also co-founded a retail tech startup. He holds a Bachelor of Engineering and a Master of Applied Science degree, both from Concordia University in Montreal, Quebec.

He lives in Canada with his wife and two daughters, and when not working, Jey loves to take long walks, read, listen to podcasts, be the chef at home, and watch UFC events. You can also check him out on LinkedIn.

list.name: Khalid Elmasry
bio: Khalid is the Director of the Engagement Project Management Office (EPMO) at Canonical.
Canonical's EPMO is a central capability spearheading Canonical's Execution Excellence Strategy and reporting to the Director of the Engagement Project Management Office and further to the COO.

Canonical's EPMO is a directive type of PMO where EPMO project managers lead Canonical's field and engineering teams in delivering a wide range of commercial customer projects as well as internal Canonical digital projects, from bare metal to cloud and high-performance computing, from AI and big data to the web and smart connected devices.

Prior to joining Canonical, Khalid worked in various countries around the world in EMEA, APAC, and North America regions, in roles spanning Operations, Customer Support, R&D Quality Assurance, Strategy Management and Execution, Organizational Excellence, and Consulting.
He holds degrees in Electrical Engineering and Telecommunications from Alexandria University and an MBA from Mannheim and ESSEC Business Schools.
Meanwhile, he lives in Ottawa, Canada.

list.name: Marina Castejon
bio: Marina Castejon is a User Experience Manager at Canonical, contributing from the Web and Design team to the mission of creating great experiences for users of Canonical’s products and websites.

Following two bachelor degrees in Business Administration and Economics, Marina decided to pursue a career in UX design in 2014. Since then, she has worked in different problem spaces, from B2B UIs with technical users to B2C e-commerce UIs. She is currently pursuing a Masters degree in UX Design. Outside work, she likes travelling, spending time outdoors and doing anything creative. You can find Marina on LinkedIn and Github.

list.name: Kathy Pelich
bio: Kathy is a Talent Scientist for our Engineering division (Information Systems and IoT Engineering). Since joining Canonical in October 2022, she has been working on standardizing and improving our interview process across the company and with a special focus on the Engineering departments.

After graduating with a degree in Translation Studies, Kathy started to work in recruitment where her background has helped her build relationships with people from all over the world. Prior to joining Canonical, she worked for Revolut for three years, where she also led the Corporate Services recruitment team.

Kathy is based in London, where she has been based ever since moving to the UK from Austria after university. Outside of work, she enjoys traveling (especially to Latin America and post-Soviet countries), literature, and scuba diving.
